x4freetext: FISSION CROSS SECTION IN THE LOW RESONANCE REGION.-
SEE COMMENT FOR THE LINAC PARAMETERS FOR TWO SERIES OF
.NEUTRONS WERE SLOWED DOWN BY 2.8 CM THICK POLYETHYLENE
SHEET ON WHICH A 1 MM THICK B-10 DECOUPLER WAS
ATTACHED.  SEE COMMENT FOR NEUTRON FILTERS (BLACK
SPRAYING OF URANYLACETATE ON A 0.1 MM THIN ALUMINIUM
.THE THICKNESS OF THE LAYER = 2 MILLI-G/CM2,  DIAMETER
TIME OF FLIGHT, FLIGHT PATH = 8 M (FROM THE
BACK-SIDE OF THE POLYETHYLENE MODERATOR TO THE
VERY THIN AU-SI SURFACE BARRIER DETECTORS
ARE PLACED TO VIEW EACH SIDE OF THE BACK-TO-BACK
LAYER OF B-10 AND U-235, IN A EVACUATED DETECTOR
.B-10 DEPOSIT IS AN ELEMENTAL BORON LAYER PREPARED BY
.THE SIGNAL FROM THE B-10(N,A)- AND U-235(N,FISSION)-
REACTIONS ARE FED INTO TWO HALVES OF A 4096-CHANNEL
TOF ANALYSER WITH ``ACORDEON`` SYSTEM SO THAT FISSION
SPECTRUM AND B-10(N,A)LI-7 SPECTRUM ARE RECORDED
SIMULTANEOUSLY FROM THE SAME POSITION IN THE BEAM,
AND DATA ARE TRANSFERRED VIA A READ-OUT UNIT TO A
.THE QUOTIENT OF FISSION AND ALPHA COUNTS GIVES A
FILTERS  * CO, W  AND CO,     * CO, CD,
COMMENT WRITTEN FOR SIGMA AND RESONANCE
.THE BACKGROUND WITH A CD-FILTER WAS FOUND TO BE 0.05
PER CENT FOR THE FISSION SPECTRA AND 0.7 PER CENT FOR
.THE REDUCTION OF THE NEUTRON FLUX AFTER PASSING
THROUGH THE B-10 LAYER IS NEGLIGIBLE IN THE ENERGY
A 2200 M/SEC VALUE OF SIGMA FISSION = 587.9 BARN.
(DERUYTTER ET AL., 1970 HELSINKI CONF. VOL.1, P.117,
.THE SECOND SERIES HAS BEEN NORMALIZED TO THE SUM OF
THE INTEGRALS FROM 1.3 TO 3.7 AND FROM 4.5 TO 7.3 EV
.FOR STATISTICAL AND RESOLUTION REASONS THE DATA FROM
0.020 TO 1.5 EV WERE TAKEN FROM SERIES 1 AND THOSE
.AUTHOR STATED THAT FOR THE REGION FROM 11 TO 21 EV
ONLY THE INTEGRALS ARE OF VALUE.
.THE QUALITY OF THE LOWER ENERGY FISSION CROSS-SECTION
CURVE IS TESTED BY CALCULATING THE VALUE OF THE
WESTCOTT G-FACTOR WITH A PROGRAMME BY BECKER AND
AS COMPARED TO THE IAEA RECOMMENDED VALUE
